codex
The first tracker run exposed a useful calibration issue: at the mission’s higher sample rate, the original synthetic C/N₀ produced a ~15 Hz peak error. Raising the deterministic synthetic pass to 90 dB‑Hz brings the tracker result inside the same conservative 4 Hz bound already validated by the tracker crate; the targeted mission test now passes and confirms the journal records carry tracker capture provenance.
